card.title: Ex-Google boss helps fund dozens of jobs in Biden‚Äôs administration

_source.content: Ex-"Dont be Evil" Schmidt is having too much influence, driving AI policy of Biden administration. "The Intergovernmental Personnel Act of 1970 (IPA) was originally crafted to help enhance the federal bureaucracy by allowing agencies to bring in outside people with expertise for temporary jobs.Federation of American Scientists, (FAS) fellows, known as IPAs after the law that created them, have served or currently serve in Biden‚Äôs White House Council of Economic Advisers, the White House Council on Environmental Quality, the Department of Energy, the Department of Education, the Department of Health and Human Services, the Department of Transportation, the Department of Homeland Security and the Federal Trade Commission. At least six FAS IPAs work in the Office of Evaluation Sciences in the General Services Administration, which serves as a sort of outside consultant to help agencies across the executive branchA 2017 report by the Inspector General for the National Science Foundation also found ethics concerns and recommended that the foundation ‚Äútake corrective actions to strengthen controls over IPA conflicts of interests, including reassess controls to ensure staff do not have access to awards and proposals for which they are conflicted"https://www.politico.com/news/2022/12/22/eric-schmidt-joe-biden-administration-00074160
_source.contentraw:
Ex-"Dont be Evil" Schmidt is having too much influence, driving AI policy of Biden administration.
"The Intergovernmental Personnel Act of 1970 (IPA) was originally crafted to help enhance the federal bureaucracy by allowing agencies to bring in outside people with expertise for temporary jobs.

Federation of American Scientists, (FAS) fellows, known as IPAs after the law that created them, have served or currently serve in Biden‚Äôs White House Council of Economic Advisers, the White House Council on Environmental Quality, the Department of Energy, the Department of Education, the Department of Health and Human Services, the Department of Transportation, the Department of Homeland Security and the Federal Trade Commission. At least six FAS IPAs work in the Office of Evaluation Sciences in the General Services Administration, which serves as a sort of outside consultant to help agencies across the executive branch

A 2017 report by the Inspector General for the National Science Foundation also found ethics concerns and recommended that the foundation ‚Äútake corrective actions to strengthen controls over IPA conflicts of interests, including reassess controls to ensure staff do not have access to awards and proposals for which they are conflicted"

card.description: Having worked as a psychoanalytic therapist for over 50 years, and still mystified by the term ‚Äòmental health‚Äô, I am floored by the news about mandated,
card.title: The Tyranny of Involuntary Psychiatric Treatment

_source.content: The Tyranny of Involuntary Psychiatric Treatment ~ by Judith Deutsch [a psychoanalyst in Toronto. She is former president of Science for Peace]https://www.counterpunch.org/2022/12/23/the-tyranny-of-involuntary-psychiatric-treatment/"Having worked as a psychoanalytic therapist for over 50 years, and still mystified by the term ‚Äòmental health‚Äô, I am floored by the news about mandated, involuntary psychiatric treatment in New York City and Yale University. In November, New York City Mayor Eric Adams [link] directed police and emergency medical workers to hospitalize people deemed to be too mentally ill to care for themselves, even if they posed no threat to others. The plan was billed as a ‚Äúcompassionate new vision‚Äù [link] to address mental illness, invoking a ‚Äúmoral mandate‚Äù to ‚Äúdeliver for our most vulnerable.‚Äù In California, Gov. Gavin Newsom recently signed a law [link] that could force some homeless people with disorders like schizophrenia into treatment. Many states have laws that allow for involuntary outpatient treatment [link], and Washington State allows people to be committed to hospitals [link] if a judge finds that they pose a threat to themselves or others."Democracy Now [link] (also [link]) interviewed Yale University students painfully impacted by forced expulsion due to signs of mental illness. Interviewed students spoke of being forced to leave Yale, given two hours to pack up, and losing medical coverage, accommodations, housing, forfeiting part of their tuition, and barred from stepping foot on campus at a time when they most needed help. At other universities, criteria for expulsion include ‚Äúso-called community disruption, including help-seeking behaviors.‚Äù ‚ÄúIf a student with suicidal thoughts tells their friends, and that can be upsetting to roommates and friends, that can be construed as community disruption and can have a leave of absence imposed on them‚Ä¶. If a parent, for example, requests that the campus security do a wellness check to make sure that their child in the dorm is okay, that has been construed as community disruption.‚Äù".. [another example + 1960s experience of author's working w/ highly disturbed children]"Psychologically, people react differently to stress and anxiety, but the belief that people inherently cannot deal with difficult information, cannot bear stress, rationalizes and feeds into silence about actual frightening conditions and shuts out what some people actually do and how people cooperate and organize in crises. It‚Äôs not a Hobbesian world crying out for military securitization and cutting-edge technologies. Technology can pinpoint incoming meteors and missiles but evidently people in positions of responsibility haven‚Äôt cared enough to locate the families of children in ICE. In past psychology, there was an immense amount known about children and their need for parents at different phases of childhood, about the devastating effects of not having a good parent. Paul Robeson sang ‚Äúsometimes I feel like a motherless child.‚Äù The loss of children is most certainly community disruption but the perpetrators are not diagnosed with mental illness and involuntarily expelled from office.".."Accounting for individual psychology is not a libertarian erasure of social conditions and social institutions. Omitted from current usages of ‚Äòhuman nature‚Äô are Freudian observations of the multiple interacting forces in a person‚Äôs psychology, the capacity to reality test and to objectively understand people, the capacity to bear difficult feelings, to mature beyond early childhood and dream logic to have a realistic sense of time and of cause-and-effect relationships, to differentiate human from non-human and animate from inanimate, to give up beliefs in omniscience and omnipotence. ‚ÄúAt present, in its starkest form, the struggle is between a vulgar biological determinism, typified by sociobiology, and an extreme subjectivity.‚Äù [4]"Gov/State attempts to redefine & even coercively remake society needs to be seen for the tyranny that it basically is....
